  "prompt": "How did the ring come to Sauron?",
  "response": "The Ring came to Sauron in two stages, with a long intervening period of being lost:\n\n**1. Sauron Forges the Ring:**\n\n*   This is the beginning of the story. Sauron, disguised as Annatar, the Lord of Gifts, aided the Elves of Eregion in creating the Rings of Power. Secretly, he forged the One Ring in the fires of Mount Doom in Mordor. While he forged it, he poured a great portion of his own power and will into the Ring, thus binding it to himself.\n\n**2. Isildur Takes the Ring:**\n\n*   When the Last Alliance of Elves and Men defeated Sauron in the War of the Last Alliance, Isildur, son of Elendil, cut the Ring from Sauron's finger with the broken hilt of his father's sword, Narsil. By taking the Ring, Isildur defeated Sauron. However, he was unwilling to destroy it, claiming it as a \"weregild\" (compensation) for the deaths of his father and brother.\n\n**3. The Ring is Lost and Then Found by Gollum:**\n\n*   Two years after the War of the Last Alliance, Isildur was ambushed by Orcs near the Gladden Fields. The Ring slipped from his finger and was lost in the Anduin river.\n*   Centuries later, a Stoor Hobbit named D\u00e9agol found the Ring in the river. His relative, Sm\u00e9agol (later known as Gollum), coveted it and murdered D\u00e9agol to claim it for himself. He hid in the Misty Mountains where he was gradually twisted by the Ring's power.\n\n**4. Bilbo Finds the Ring:**\n\n*   After nearly five centuries, Bilbo Baggins, during his adventures in *The Hobbit*, stumbled upon Gollum's lair and found the Ring after a riddle game with Gollum. Bilbo escaped with the Ring, unaware of its true nature.\n\n**5. Gandalf Discovers the Ring's True Nature:**\n\n*   Years later, Gandalf the Grey began to suspect the nature of Bilbo's Ring. After extensive research and consulting with Elrond, he confirmed that it was indeed the One Ring of Sauron.\n\n**6. The Ring is Sent to Frodo:**\n\n*   Bilbo eventually left the Ring to his nephew, Frodo Baggins, setting in motion the events of *The Lord of the Rings*.\n\n**7. The Ring is Destroyed by Frodo:**\n\n*   After a long and difficult journey, Frodo, with the help of Samwise Gamgee, brought the Ring to Mount Doom in Mordor. At the last moment, Frodo claimed the Ring for himself, but Gollum seized it and fell into the fires.\n\n**In summary, the Ring did not come directly back to Sauron after Isildur took it. Rather, it was lost for many years, then found by Gollum, then Bilbo, and finally carried by Frodo until it was destroyed in Mount Doom.**\n",
